10 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Powers of department -- rulemaking. (1) The department may
11 prescribe rules not inconsistent with the provisions of [sections 1 through 5] for the detailed and efficient
12 administration of [sections 1 through 5]. All rules and orders promulgated must be published promptly and a
13 copy distributed to each wholesale licensee. The department is authorized to adopt rules for the effective
14 collection and refund of the tax imposed by [sections 1 through 5].
15 (2) The department may conduct inquiries and hearings, and any member of the department or
16 any agent may administer oaths and take testimony under oath relative to the matter of inquiry. The director
17 may subpoena witnesses and require the production of books, papers, and documents. The director, after the
18 hearing, shall make findings and issue an order in writing. The findings and order must be filed in the office of
19 the department and must be open for public inspection.
20 (3) The department may appoint additional assistants as required to carry out the provisions of
21 [sections 1 through 5].
22 (4) The department is authorized to employ clerical and field assistants necessary to properly
23 administer the provisions of [sections 1 through 5].
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Tax imposed -- collection and enforcement. (1) (a) A tax on the
26 purchase of vapor products for consumption, use, or any purpose other than resale in the regular course of
27 business is imposed and must be precollected by the wholesaler and paid to the state.
28 (b) The tax on vapor products that contain nicotine is 20% of the wholesale price.
